Class SerialTypes.BackingInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.vcenter.vm.hardware.SerialTypes.BackingInfo

    public static final class SerialTypes.BackingInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, StaticStructure
    The BackingInfo class contains information about the physical resource backing a virtual serial port.

      • getNoRxLoss

        public java.lang.Boolean getNoRxLoss()
        Flag that enables optimized data transfer over the pipe. When the value is true, the host buffers data to prevent data overrun. This allows the virtual machine to read all of the data transferred over the pipe with no data loss. This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getType() is one of SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_SERVER or SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_CLIENT.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

      • setNoRxLoss

This allows the virtual machine to read all of the data transferred over the pipe with no data loss. This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getType() is one of SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_SERVER or SerialTypes.BackingType.PIPE_CLIENT.

      • getNetworkLocation

        public java.net.URI getNetworkLocation()
        URI specifying the location of the network service backing the virtual serial port.
        • If getType() is SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_SERVER, this property is the location used by clients to connect to this server. The hostname part of the URI should either be empty or should specify the address of the host on which the virtual machine is running.
        • If getType() is SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_CLIENT, this property is the location used by the virtual machine to connect to the remote server.
        This property is optional and it is only relevant when the value of getType() is one of SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_SERVER or SerialTypes.BackingType.NETWORK_CLIENT.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

      • _validate

        public void _validate()
        Description copied from interface: StaticStructure
        Validates the state of the discriminated unions and HasFieldsOf restrictions (if any) in this Java language binding Structure.

        More precisely, for each union: given value of the discriminant/tag field (@UnionTag in the IDL) of an union in this structure, validates that:

      • all fields of the union required for that value of the discriminant are set
      • fields of the union that are not allowed for that value of the discriminant are not set
      • any other fields of the structure (not participating in the union) do not affect the validation result
